WoWPython -- History of visible changes.

Copyright (C) 2004, Team Python
See the end for copying conditions.

Please submit WoWPython bug reports at:
  http://sourceforge.net/tracker/?func=add&group_id=114767&atid=669366


Version 0.8.9

* Cleaned the player login code and ObjectMgr creation helper
  functions. - DeathCheese
* Added support for a WoWPython.conf file which can contain console
  commands to be executed on server start. - Follower
* Fixed a bug that would displays players as naked after logging out
  and then back in. - DeathCheese
* Fixed Cinematics now will only start if at starting location
* Quest code mainenance.  No new features, but now existing features
  work correctly.  Most of it. - DeathCheese
* In Worldserver::disconnect_client() LogoutPlayer() nulls current
  char before we have a chance to remove it from InRange lists


Version 0.8.8

* Added Monster Movement - Asus coded WantedMan updated cvs
* Added !summon and !appear


Version 0.8.7

* Multiple levels of GM - Battyone
* Redesigned Command Prefixes - Battyone
* Spell Trainers no longer train duplicate spells - R-o-n-n-y
* LAN Mode fix - Eggy
* .mount has a level requirement for non-gm - Battyone
* .mount gives proper mounts - Europa
* .mount for gm has no lvl requirement - Battyone
* Kalimdor Spawns work correctly - anonymous (no name on patch tracker)
* !broadcast command implemented - Europa
* .mount sets correct mount speed - Battyone
* .dismout sets correct walk speed - Battyone
* Seperated GM levels - DeathCheese
* Updatemask correct - DeathCheese
* worldport no longer crashes client (still buggy with alot of creatures)


Version 0.8.6

* Trainers are now managed in Database - Angelic|999
* Cosmetic changes to versioning - Battyone
* New .sql file - Battyone
* Beginnings of updatemask fix - DeathCheese
* .speed Command - RandomGuy
* Added LANhost - Eggy


Version 0.8.5-pre3

* Initial Release


